215
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:29,920
But so, if you come from an Heideggerian understanding, every way of being that you see has three potential stances toward it.

216
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:36,640
You can either be indifferent, or you can choose inauthentically, or you can choose authentically.

217
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:41,439
This is kind of the way you put, as I think about it, you position yourself towards that way of being.

218
00:24:41,439 --> 00:24:44,559
And it can be either in three ways.

219
00:24:45,519 --> 00:25:09,200
If you are indifferent, this would be a way that you've never come to question your social role, or you've never experienced any unrest or unsettlement about the roles that are potential for you, and you've never really thought about the finitude of your being, but you just go on with everything as you're born into the order and the way of being.

220
00:25:09,199 --> 00:25:11,920
You just continue it without questions.

221
00:25:12,239 --> 00:25:16,800
And Heidegger does stress that it's not that being indifferent is not a negative.

222
00:25:16,799 --> 00:25:44,199
It's the other two things that are interesting to me here because the inauthentic choice is one, let's say now in puberty, you suddenly realize that you are mortal and you this great unsettledness comes over you and you're very anxious about your existence and now what you do is you choose a social role but you do that as though you reach for a life preserver while drowning.

223
00:25:44,199 --> 00:25:52,039
You choose this role and you really stick to that role because thereby you can settle your anxiety.

224
00:25:52,039 --> 00:25:54,920
And that would be an inauthentic choice.

225
00:25:55,239 --> 00:26:12,119
And then the last option is an authentic choice in which your anxiety would remain, in which you would be aware that this role can't save you from it, but that you would express that in the way that you accept that role or that you act that role.

226
00:26:12,439 --> 00:26:19,880
And now my reading or my thesis is that Aeneas acts inauthentic and Dido acts authentic.

227
00:26:20,519 --> 00:26:30,759
I think Aeneas remains inauthentic because he only goes along with his duty, it's not really chosen and he is like this dog dragged by the cart.

228
00:26:31,080 --> 00:26:38,439
And I think that Dido is authentic because she actively chooses her stance and sees her situation.

229
00:26:38,759 --> 00:26:46,119
And she has a little monologue with herself where she weighs all of her options.

